@NODE RELEASE
RELEASE INFORMATION
	FlushMem  is  placed  to  be in Puplic Domain and may be spreaded
through  PD-libraries.   You  are  not allowed to change the code nor add
anything  on  the code.  I still have the copyright.  The author will not
take  any responsibilities of damage caused by this program.  It has been
tested  on  several  Amigas,  and  no major bugs have occured during this
time...
@ENDNODE

@NODE INTRODUCTION
INTRODUCTION
	FlushMem is a command that clears memory from unused bytes.  When
exiting a program, it might leave some libraries in memory.  This utility
will  clear  it.   CED  is  a fine example of this.  Just load CED, press
Amiga  plus  'M' to switch screen, and run, let's say, filemaster.  Start
it  with  'filemaster  -s'  so  that  you can see the bar.  Quit CED, run
FlushMem and watch the result.  Even 50 kilos could be saved on this!
@ENDNODE

@NODE USAGE
USAGE
	This  utility has no options, so just load it.  A message appears
to tell you that FlushMem was loaded.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FUTURE
FUTURE PLANS
	I  will  append some extra features to coming versions.  Features
like AddMem and DriveClick-Killer will be added.  I will also try to keep
this  utility  KS1.3  compatible,  but  I  can't  give  you any promises.
Suggestions are more than welcome!
@ENDNODE

